{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place garlic, ginger, chillies and sesame oil into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add chicken and cook <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed <\/nobr>.","Stir with aid of spatula to ensure even cooking. Add Chinese rice wine, dark soy sauce, sugar and light soy sauce and cook <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed <\/nobr>.","Stir with aid of spatula to ensure even cooking, then cook for a further <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed <\/nobr> or until chicken is cooked.","Stir with aid of spatula. Add basil leaves and cook <nobr>1 min\/Varoma\/speed <\/nobr>. Transfer into a serving bowl and serve with sides of choice (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 garlic cloves","3 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","1 - 2 fresh long red chillies, trimmed, deseeded and cut into pieces","10 g sesame oil","1000 g chicken winglets (see Tips)","40 g Chinese rice wine (Shaoxing)","30 g dark soy sauce (see Tips)","25 g sugar (rock sugar - see Tips)","60 g light soy sauce","2 sprigs fresh basil, leaves only"]}],"id":"r179804","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-4truexJ9Ero\/XZQHCsNXGHI\/AAAAAAAAcEk\/PCXTddbztOUSCSDLyKwnxbXD_gbUAKxDACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_blNielOOpw1ZeeLx.png","title":"Three cup chicken","publishedAt":"2018-01-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"46.2 g","fat":"47 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"12.5 g","calories":"2763 kJ \/ 657 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving bowl","hintsAndTricks":["You can use winglets or drumettes for this recipe.","Rock sugar is crystallised, refined sugar available at most Asian food stores. Alternatively, you can use white sugar.","Dark soy sauce is richer, aged longer and saltier than light soy sauce and sweeter due to added sugars. Light soy sauce is thinner, saltier and more commonly used as a light seasoning or dipping sauce. Both are available at most major supermarkets.","We served our dish with cooked white rice.","This dish's name derives from the three cups of sauces that were typically used to make the dish."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","4 portions"]}